724470f-a.text:
732 West End Avenue, east side, between 95th Streets, one of three houses built in the late 1880's. The adjoining vacant lot extends down to the 95th Street corner, and has never been built on, nor will be till late in the 1920's.

Compare this with the picture of 734-38 taken about the same time, and with the view of the new building erected on the 96th Street corner about 1908.

About 1910.
